FuTRES_def: identifier for the materialSample that is globally unique
refers to a lot or single specimen or a single indvidual of the same taxon
example: UUID perhaps in a previous dataset

FuTRES_def: a globally unique identifier that relates to the Occurrence (as opposed to the digital record of the occurrence)
identifier of a distinct individual (e.g. single bone within an associated skeleton)
example: UUID or we will provide one

FuTRES_def: code or abbreviation for the institution or museum
example: NMNH for the National Museum of Natural History

FuTRES_def: An identifier for the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record
code or abbreviation for the collection within the museum
number assigned to the specimen by the institution or museum
A list of previous catalog numbers or human-used identifiers for the indivudal occurrence
lowest taxnomic indentification for a specimen
A list (concatenated and separated) of previous assignments of names to the individual
number assigned to the field site or lot
latitude in decimal degrees between -90 and 90
longitude in decimal degrees between -180 and 180
horizontal distance in meters from the decimalLatidue and decimalLongitude
original latitude of site
original longitude of site
lower limit of elevation (above sea level) in meters (same as maximum if it is a single point value)
upper limit of elevation (above sea level) in meters (same as minimum if it is a single point value)
description of site
original description of site
example: 3 miles west of Gainesville or underneath of Guatemala City

FuTRES_def: country of observation or collection
state of porvince of observation or collection
original date and time of observation or collection
example: date of collection event, not of measurement; Jun 1847

FuTRES_def: Comments about observation or collection event
description or reference to method of trait measurement
Condition of the specimen for trait measurement
sex of the individual being measured
original description of life stage of individual
Age class or life stage of the individual being measured
reproductive condition of the individual at time of measurement

numerical value or range indicating how old including the unit such as hours, days, weeks, months, or years the individual is a time of death (paleo and zooarchaeological), collection (neoecological), or observation (non-specimen observations)

numerical value indicating how old in hours, days, weeks, months, or years the individual is a time of death (paleo and zooarchaeological), collection (neoecological), or observation (non-specimen observations).
unit for the ageValue in hour, day, week, month, or year
free text field for description of method for determining ageValue
trait and anatomical or physiological feature being measured
value of measurement
unit for the measurementValue
description of method used for measurement
URI pointing to description of method for measurement
side of individual the measurement was taken
name of measurer
date measurement was taken
value of measurement error by the measurer
name of bone
condition of the specimen
example: burning: calcined, animal alteration: none, taphonomy: medial side eroded slightly, conservation treatment: alvar

FuTRES_def: portion of the element represented, can be descriptive (eg distal epiphysis) or proportional (75% of diaphysis)
identifier for the geologicalContext such as stratigraphy
lower limit of the age of the specimen determined by some chronometricAgeProtocol
earliest geochronologic eon from which the specimen was collected
latest geochronologic eon from which the specimen was collected
earliest geochronologic era from which the specimen was collected
latest geochronologic era from which the specimen was collected
earliest geochronologic era from which the specimen was collected
latest geochronologic era from which the specimen was collected
earliest geochronologic epoch from which the specimen was collected
latest geochronologic epoch from which the specimen was collected
earliest geochronologic age from which the specimen was collected
latest geochronologic age from which the specimen was collected
lowest geological biostratigraphic zone from which the specimen was collected
highest geological biostratigraphic zone from which the specimen was collected
units for the minimumChronometricAge
need: required if there is a value in minimumChronometricAge

FuTRES_def: upper limit of the age of the specimen determined by some chronometricAgeProtocol
units for the maximumChronometricAge
need: needed if there is a value in maximumChronometricAge

FuTRES_def: free text or reference to dating method for minimum and maximum chronomtericAge
need: suggested if do either maximum or minimum chronometricAge

FuTRES_def: standard deviation of dating method
need: suggested if do either maximum or minimum ChronometricAge

FuTRES_def: depth below the surface
the lesser depth below the surface in meters
the greater depth below the surface in meters
name of the lowest hierarchical geologic stratigraphy for where the specimen was collected
name of the lithographic group from which the specimen was collected
name of the lithographic formation from which the specimen was collected
name of the lithographic member from which the specimen was collected
name of the lithographic bed from which the specimen was collected

the names (not dates) of the regional and local occupational periods to which these specimens pertain. use as many names as necessary to fully define the regional and local occupational periods - these can be either temporally or spatio-temporally defined

names of the cultural groups with which the occupants of the site would have been affiliated during the occupational period to which these specimens pertain - these are modern names where original culture names are unknown
the culturally defined region or regions of which this site was a part during the occupational period to which these specimens pertain - spatially or spatio-temporally defined
description of the context(s) to which these specimens pertain
a related resource that is referenced or otherwise pointed to by the described resource
example: DOI or Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology citation format

FuTRES_def: place for notes related to observation event
URL to archived dataset or contact for person(s) who collected the data
a note that more precise or other information does exist but is not provided
example: specific locations withheld to protect endangered species, see collection manager for additional detail
